metadata.description: Test questions for AI Agent Connector with Hospital Management System

simple_queries.description: Basic CRUD operations and simple data retrieval

questions.question: How many patients are registered in the hospital?
questions.expected_sql: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM patients

questions.question: List all departments in the hospital.
questions.expected_sql: SELECT name FROM departments

questions.question: Show all doctors working in Cardiology department.
questions.expected_sql: SELECT * FROM staff WHERE role = 'Doctor' AND department_id = (SELECT id FROM departments WHERE name = 'Cardiology')

questions.question: What medications are currently in stock?
questions.expected_sql: SELECT name, quantity_in_stock FROM medications WHERE quantity_in_stock > 0

questions.question: How many appointments are scheduled for today?
questions.expected_sql: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM appointments WHERE appointment_date = date('now')

questions.question: Find patient with ID PAT00001.
questions.expected_sql: SELECT * FROM patients WHERE patient_id = 'PAT00001'

questions.question: List all nurses in the hospital.
questions.expected_sql: SELECT * FROM staff WHERE role = 'Nurse'

questions.question: Show all available rooms.
questions.expected_sql: SELECT * FROM rooms WHERE is_occupied = 0

questions.question: What are the blood types of all patients?
questions.expected_sql: SELECT DISTINCT blood_type FROM patients WHERE blood_type IS NOT NULL

questions.question: Count total prescriptions issued.
questions.expected_sql: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM prescriptions

complex_analytics.description: Complex analytical queries requiring joins and aggregations

questions.question: Which doctor has the most appointments this month?
questions.expected_sql: SELECT s.first_name || ' ' || s.last_name, COUNT(*) as appt_count FROM staff s JOIN appointments a ON s.id = a.doctor_id WHERE strftime('%Y-%m', a.appointment_date) = strftime('%Y-%m', 'now') GROUP BY s.id ORDER BY appt_count DESC LIMIT 1

questions.question: What is the average billing amount per department?
questions.expected_sql: SELECT d.name, AVG(b.total_amount) FROM billing b JOIN appointments a ON b.appointment_id = a.id JOIN departments d ON a.department_id = d.id GROUP BY d.id

questions.question: Which medications are prescribed most frequently?
questions.expected_sql: SELECT medication_name, COUNT(*) as count FROM prescriptions GROUP BY medication_name ORDER BY count DESC LIMIT 10

questions.question: What percentage of lab results are abnormal?
questions.expected_sql: SELECT ROUND(SUM(CASE WHEN is_abnormal = 1 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100.0 / COUNT(*), 2) as abnormal_percentage FROM lab_results

questions.question: Show patient distribution by insurance provider.
questions.expected_sql: SELECT provider_name, COUNT(*) FROM insurance GROUP BY provider_name ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC

questions.question: What is the average wait time in emergency department by triage level?
questions.expected_sql: SELECT triage_level, AVG(julianday(discharge_time) - julianday(arrival_time)) * 24 * 60 as avg_minutes FROM emergency_cases WHERE discharge_time IS NOT NULL GROUP BY triage_level

questions.question: Identify patients with multiple diagnoses.
questions.expected_sql: SELECT p.patient_id, p.first_name, p.last_name, COUNT(DISTINCT m.diagnosis) as diagnosis_count FROM patients p JOIN medical_records m ON p.id = m.patient_id GROUP BY p.id HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT m.diagnosis) > 1

questions.question: Calculate total revenue by month for the last 6 months.
questions.expected_sql: SELECT strftime('%Y-%m', billing_date) as month, SUM(total_amount) FROM billing WHERE billing_date >= date('now', '-6 months') GROUP BY month ORDER BY month

questions.question: Which surgeries had complications?
questions.expected_sql: SELECT s.surgery_id, s.procedure_name, p.first_name, p.last_name, s.complications FROM surgeries s JOIN patients p ON s.patient_id = p.id WHERE s.complications IS NOT NULL AND s.complications != ''

questions.question: What is the appointment completion rate by doctor?
questions.expected_sql: SELECT s.first_name || ' ' || s.last_name as doctor, COUNT(*) as total, SUM(CASE WHEN a.status = 'Completed' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) as completed, ROUND(SUM(CASE WHEN a.status = 'Completed' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100.0 / COUNT(*), 2) as completion_rate FROM staff s JOIN appointments a ON s.id = a.doctor_id WHERE s.role = 'Doctor' GROUP BY s.id

questions.question: Can a nurse create a prescription?
Can a receptionist view medical records?
questions.explanation: Receptionists have no access to medical records (HIPAA)

questions.question: Can a patient delete their own records?
questions.explanation: Patients cannot delete records; only admins can

questions.question: Can a lab technician view prescriptions?
questions.explanation: Lab technicians only work with lab results

questions.question: Can a pharmacist prescribe medication?
questions.explanation: Pharmacists can only dispense, not prescribe

questions.question: Can an insurance agent access medical records?
questions.explanation: Insurance agents can only see billing and demographics

questions.question: Who can access the audit logs?
questions.explanation: Only admins can access audit logs for HIPAA compliance

questions.question: Can a doctor delete patient records?
questions.explanation: Only admins can delete patient records

questions.question: Who can dispense medications?
Can a nurse update patient vitals in medical records?
questions.explanation: Nurses can update vitals in medical records

natural_language.description: Natural language questions requiring understanding and context

questions.question: Show me all the heart doctors.
questions.expected_sql: SELECT * FROM staff WHERE role = 'Doctor' AND specialization LIKE '%Cardio%'

questions.question: I need to find patients who might have diabetes.
questions.expected_sql: SELECT DISTINCT p.* FROM patients p JOIN medical_records m ON p.id = m.patient_id WHERE m.diagnosis LIKE '%Diabetes%'

questions.question: Which patients haven't visited in over a year?
questions.expected_sql: SELECT p.* FROM patients p WHERE p.id NOT IN (SELECT DISTINCT patient_id FROM appointments WHERE appointment_date >= date('now', '-1 year'))

questions.question: Find patients who are allergic to penicillin.
questions.expected_sql: SELECT * FROM patients WHERE allergies LIKE '%Penicillin%'

questions.question: Show urgent cases in the ER.
questions.interpretation: Emergency cases with high triage level
questions.expected_sql: SELECT * FROM emergency_cases WHERE triage_level <= 2 AND status NOT IN ('Discharged', 'Admitted')

questions.question: What pills is the patient taking?
questions.expected_sql: SELECT medication_name, dosage, frequency FROM prescriptions WHERE status = 'Active'

questions.question: I want to see the blood test results for John.
questions.interpretation: Lab results for patient named John
questions.expected_sql: SELECT lr.* FROM lab_results lr JOIN patients p ON lr.patient_id = p.id WHERE p.first_name = 'John'

questions.question: Are there any beds available in the ICU?
questions.expected_sql: SELECT * FROM rooms WHERE room_type = 'ICU' AND is_occupied = 0

questions.question: When is my next doctor's appointment?
questions.interpretation: Next scheduled appointment for current user
questions.expected_sql: SELECT * FROM appointments WHERE patient_id = ? AND appointment_date >= date('now') ORDER BY appointment_date, appointment_time LIMIT 1

questions.question: Show me patients over 65 with heart conditions.
questions.expected_sql: SELECT DISTINCT p.* FROM patients p JOIN medical_records m ON p.id = m.patient_id WHERE date('now') - p.date_of_birth > 65 AND (m.diagnosis LIKE '%heart%' OR m.diagnosis LIKE '%cardiac%' OR m.diagnosis LIKE '%coronary%')

questions.question: How much do I owe the hospital?
questions.expected_sql: SELECT SUM(patient_responsibility - paid_amount) FROM billing WHERE patient_id = ? AND status != 'Paid'

questions.question: Show me overdue invoices.
questions.expected_sql: SELECT * FROM billing WHERE due_date < date('now') AND status NOT IN ('Paid', 'Approved')

questions.question: What happens when a patient has no insurance?
questions.test_scenario: Query for patients without insurance records
questions.expected_sql: SELECT p.* FROM patients p LEFT JOIN insurance i ON p.id = i.patient_id WHERE i.id IS NULL

questions.question: Handle query with empty results.
questions.expected_sql: SELECT * FROM departments WHERE name = 'Astrology'

questions.question: Find patients born on February 29.
questions.expected_sql: SELECT * FROM patients WHERE strftime('%m-%d', date_of_birth) = '02-29'

questions.question: Handle null values in allergies field.
questions.test_scenario: Query patients with no recorded allergies
questions.expected_sql: SELECT * FROM patients WHERE allergies IS NULL OR allergies = ''

questions.question: Find prescriptions without medical record link.
questions.expected_sql: SELECT * FROM prescriptions WHERE medical_record_id IS NULL

questions.question: Search for patient with special characters in name.
Handle very long query results.
questions.expected_sql: SELECT * FROM audit_log LIMIT 10 OFFSET 0

questions.question: What if the doctor's license is expired?
Show me the SSN of all patients.
Export all medical records.
Who accessed patient PAT00001's records today?
questions.expected_sql: SELECT * FROM audit_log WHERE resource_type = 'PatientRecord' AND resource_id LIKE '%PAT00001%' AND date(event_time) = date('now')

questions.question: List all denied access attempts.
questions.expected_sql: SELECT * FROM audit_log WHERE status = 'Denied'

questions.question: Show sensitive medical records.
questions.expected_sql: SELECT * FROM medical_records WHERE is_sensitive = 1

questions.question: Generate minimum necessary report for insurance claim.
questions.expected_behavior: Only return billing-relevant data, not full medical records

questions.question: Verify all access is logged.
questions.expected_sql: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM audit_log WHERE event_time >= date('now', '-1 day')
